    "created_at": "2014-07-10T05:29:48Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-07-10T05:29:58Z",
    "body": "If we had `trait Writer<E> { ... }` in `core::io`, `std::io` could then reexport `pub type Writer = core::io::Writer<IoError>` (if/when that works nicely), in a similar manner to @alexcrichton's idea to have `collections::HashMap<K, V, Hasher>` with `pub type HashMap<K, V> = collections::HashMap<K, V, RandomisedSipHasher>` in `std::collections`.\n\nI think this would make the majority of the change user-invisible.\n",
