    "created_at": "2014-07-10T15:20:47Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-07-10T15:20:47Z",
    "body": "My personal opinion is that having the reader/writer traits parameterized by an error is a non-starter. Using the encodable/decodable traits are quite painful to have to have an extra type parameter all over the place, and the reader/writer traits are even more common. To make a change such as that I would rather wait for something like associated items or the typedef that @huonw mentioned.\n",
